  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a 32-bit value encoding four ASCII characters, used to identify OpenType font tables, axes, and features.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFourByteTag` is a 32-bit value that encodes four ASCII characters, widely used
in OpenType and TrueType font tables to identify axes, tables, and features.
The first character occupies the high byte and the fourth character the low byte
(`(c1 << 24) | (c2 << 16) | (c3 << 8) | c4`).

Common tag strings include `'wght'` (weight), `'wdth'` (width), and `'ital'`
(italic). The type implicitly converts to and from `uint` and supports parsing
from a string with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFourByteTag.Parse(System.String)>.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create from four characters
var weightTag = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'g', 'h', 't');

// Parse from a string (shorter strings are padded with spaces)
var tag = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wdth");

// Convert back to string
Console.WriteLine(tag.ToString()); // "wdth"
```
]]></format></remarks>
